# Convention: each doc's `# H1` is its sidebar label. Plain entries below
# inherit the H1, so adding a new doc usually requires no change to this file
# (it auto-slots into the trailing `- ...` rest placeholder). The friendly-
# title syntax `Sidebar Label: filename.md` remains available as an escape
# hatch when an H1 must intentionally differ from the sidebar — but in
# practice we keep them aligned so this file stays minimal.
nav:
  - overview.md
  - Integration:
      - integration.md
      - viewer_contract_v1_8.md
      - capture_and_replay.md
      - demoapp.md
      - persistence_patterns.md
  - Authoring:
      - admin_authoring_guide.md
      - model_authoring_guide.md
      - marker_pipeline.md
      - demo_walkthrough.md
  - ...

# index.md is the auto-rendered home page (linked from the site title); it
# should be reachable but not duplicated in the sidebar. architecture.md and
# performance.md are BPViewer-maintainer-internal — they cite source files
# under src/viewer/ that aren't published in the integration kit, so they're
# kept rendered (so any inbound link still resolves) but hidden from the
# public sidebar. subscriber_materials_plan.md is also internal-planning
# (BPViewer-side architecture for a future feature, not CustomApp-facing).
# New "draft" docs you want deployed but hidden from the sidebar can be added
# here too.
not_in_nav: |
  index.md
  docs_publishing.md
  architecture.md
  performance.md
  subscriber_materials_plan.md
